## What's included

A complete, runnable Express portfolio site backed by **SQLite** (no separate DB server to install):

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `package.json` | Dependency manifest |
| `server.js` | Express app: routes, session auth, image uploads, error handling |
| `db.js` | SQLite setup + data-access helpers; auto-seeds the owner account |
| `views/` | EJS templates — public grid, login, admin dashboard, project form |
| `public/css/style.css` | Responsive dark-theme styling |
| `.env.example` | Configurable port / secret / owner credentials |
| `README.md` | Run instructions (port 5053) |
| `.gitignore` | Excludes `node_modules`, `data/`, uploads, `.env` |

## How it works

- **Public page** (`/`) renders all projects in a responsive auto-fill grid (image, title, description, external link).
- **Owner login** (`/login`) — bcrypt-hashed passwords, sessions persisted in SQLite via `connect-sqlite3`.
- **Dashboard** (`/admin`, auth-gated) — create / edit / delete projects with image upload (multer, image-only, 5 MB cap). Editing keeps the existing image if no new file is given.
- First run auto-creates an owner: **`admin` / `changeme`** (overridable via `ADMIN_USER`/`ADMIN_PASS`).
- Listens on **port 5053** by default (`PORT` overrides).

## To run it

```bash
npm install
npm start
# open http://localhost:5053  → log in at /login with admin / changeme
```

